  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ ./geth version\r\nGeth\r\nVersion: 1.9.0-unstable\r\nArchitecture: amd64\r\nProtocol Versions: [63 62]\r\nNetwork Id: 1\r\nGo Version: go1.12.1\r\nOperating System: darwin\r\n```\r\n\r\nCommit hash : df488975bd4bc514a01a3157d52dafd0118a4a05\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nAble to trace all the blocks in the chain between block \"0x0\" and block \"0x14832\".\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\n- First, the error an error is printed `Attempted to dereference the trie cache meta root`. (Probably around here: https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/master/eth/api_tracer.go#L297-L315)\r\n- Then I get an error that insufficient balance is available for transfer (probably from around here: https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/master/eth/api_tracer.go#L292-L296)\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\nTerminal 1\r\n1. `./geth --mine=false --datadir=$YOUR_DATA_DIR --syncmode=full --gcmode=archive --maxpeers 0 console`\r\n\r\nTermnial 2:\r\n1. `nc -U $YOUR_DATA_DIR/geth.ipc`\r\n2. paste `{\"id\": 1, \"method\": \"debug_subscribe\", \"params\": [\"traceChain\", \"0x0\", \"0x14832\", {\"tracer\": \"{\\r\\narguments: [],\\r\\nstep: function(log, db) {if (false) {\\r\\n    this.arguments.push({x: log.stack.peek(1).toString(16), y:  log.stack.peek(2).toString(16)})\\r\\n}\\r\\n},\\r\\nresult: function(){ return this.arguments;}, \\r\\nfault: function(){}\\r\\n}\\r\\n\", \"reexec\":0}]}`\r\n\r\nWait a bit, I received the following messages:\r\n\r\n1. `ERROR[03-26|17:03:29.756] Attempted to dereference the trie cache meta root`\r\n2. `WARN [03-26|17:15:10.493] Chain tracing failed                     start=0 end=84018 transactions=18161 elapsed=48.668734125s err=\"insufficient balance for transfer\"`",
